ttp://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1707, \"end\": 1710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6283115251200655e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more detailed discussions\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1544}, {\"ngram\": \"the Preferred Hosts\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"the aim\", \"from\": 1625, \"to\": 1632}, {\"ngram\": \"both editions\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"the 142nd IOC Session\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1683}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1687, \"to\": 1691}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opening ceremony of the Winter Olympic Games at the Rice-Eccles Olympic Stadium in Salt Lake City, Utah, February 8, 2002.\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1817, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"score\": 0.9999403681997435, \"rank\": 5.9443121227034094e-05, \"text\": \"Utah\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Utah\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1734}, {\"ngram\": \"the Winter Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1762}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rice-Eccles Olympic Stadium\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1797}, {\"ngram\": \"Salt Lake City\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1815}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP So far, there is no second bidder competing with Salt Lake City, which included its Games vision and concept along with site plans, sustainability studies and financial information in the Preferred Host Submission, according to Reuters.\", \"from\": 1841, \"to\": 2083, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1896, \"end\": 1910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2002_Winter_Olympi